Iris Dataset Analysis Using Pandas
The Iris dataset is commonly used for data analysis and machine learning practice. 
Using Pandas and Seaborn, the dataset is loaded and analyzed statistically. The describe() function provides overall statistical information,
while groupby() helps analyze data species-wise. This process is called Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), which helps understand 
data patterns before building ML models.

